                                        Keiko Nobumoto, character designer Toshihiro Kawamoto, mechanical designer Kimitoshi
                                        Yamane, and composer Yoko Kanno, who are collectively billed as Hajime Yatate.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4">
                            <img class="w-14" src="/assets/edit_icon.png" alt="save-icon">
                            <img class="h-24 md:-rotate-90" src="/assets/arrow-drawn-black.png" alt="arrow">
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Modify Articles</h3>
                            <div class="flex items-center m-8">
                                <div class="article-preview">
                                    <div class="article-title">Cowboy Bebop (Anime)</div>
                                    <div class="article-content">
                                        <span class="font-semibold">[My own review --->]</span> Cowboy Bebop is a Japanese anime television series characterized by its neo-noir and space Western genres. It was broadcast on TV Tokyo and Wowow from 1998 to 1999. The series was created and animated by the studio Sunrise. The production team, collectively known as Hajime Yatate, included director Shinichirō Watanabe, screenwriter Keiko Nobumoto, character designer Toshihiro Kawamoto, mechanical designer Kimitoshi Yamane, and composer Yoko Kanno.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex justify-center items-center w-full mt-4">
                        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-center">Read articles from your library and modify them as you please without any restriction.</p>
                    </div>
                </section>


                <section class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center shadow-lg p-6 my-6 rounded-md min-h-[600px]">
                    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row w-full justify-center items-center gap-10">
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center mr-4">
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">From Library</h3>
                            <img class="max-w-[500px]" src="/assets/my_library.png" alt="search_image">
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4">
                            <img class="w-14" src="/assets/add_icon.png" alt="save-icon">
                            <img class="h-24 md:-rotate-90" src="/assets/arrow-drawn-black.png" alt="arrow">
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Create Articles</h3>
                            <div class="flex items-center m-8">
                                <div class="article-preview">
                                    <div class="article-title">My Own Title</div>
                                    <div class="article-content">
                                        This is my personal article written and created by me. Available in my library so that i can read it any time i want to, i can modify it and delete it as i please.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex justify-center items-center w-full mt-4">
                        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-center">Create your own article and save it in your library. You're the only one who can have access to it.</p>
                    </div>
                </section>



                <!-- Sezione base test-->
                <section class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center shadow-lg p-6 my-6 rounded-md min-h-[600px]">
                    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row w-full justify-center items-center gap-10">
                        <div class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center p-6 my-6 rounded-md">
                            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Library</h2>
                            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                                <div class="article-preview border p-4 rounded-md shadow-md">
                                    <div class="article-title text-xl font-semibold">Cowboy Bebop</div>
                                    <div class="article-content">
                                        Cowboy Bebop is a Japanese neo-noir space Western anime television series which
                                        aired on TV Tokyo and Wowow from 1998 to 1999. It was created and animated by
                                        Sunrise, led by a production team of director Shinichirō Watanabe, screenwriter
                                        Keiko Nobumoto, character designer Toshihiro Kawamoto, mechanical designer Kimitoshi
                                        Yamane, and composer Yoko Kanno, who are collectively billed as Hajime Yatate.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="article-preview border p-4 rounded-md shadow-md">
                                    <div class="article-title text-xl font-semibold">Neon Genesis Evangelion</div>
                                    <div class="article-content">
                                        Neon Genesis Evangelion is a Japanese mecha anime television series produced by
                                        Gainax and Tatsunoko Production, directed by Hideaki Anno, and broadcast on TV Tokyo
                                        from October 1995 to March 1996.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="article-preview border p-4 rounded-md shadow-md">
                                    <div class="article-title text-xl font-semibold">One Piece</div>
                                    <div class="article-content">
                                        One Piece is a Japanese manga series written and illustrated by Eiichiro Oda. It has
                                        been serialized in Shueisha's shōnen manga magazine Weekly Shōnen Jump since July 1997.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="article-preview border p-4 rounded-md shadow-md">
                                    <div class="article-title text-xl font-semibold">Attack on Titan</div>
                                    <div class="article-content">
                                        Attack on Titan is a Japanese manga series written and illustrated by Hajime Isayama.
                                        It is set in a world where humanity lives inside cities surrounded by enormous walls due to
                                        the sudden appearance of the Titans.
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4">
                            <img class="w-14" src="/assets/add_icon.png" alt="save-icon">
                            <img class="h-24 md:-rotate-90" src="/assets/arrow-drawn-black.png" alt="arrow">
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Create Articles</h3>
                            <div class="flex items-center m-8">
                                <div class="article-preview">
                                    <div class="article-title">My Own Title</div>
                                    <div class="article-content">
                                        This is my personal article written and created by me. Available in my library so that i can read it any time i want to, i can modify it and delete it as i please.
